| **ESP32-CAM**                                              |                    **ESP32-DEV** | **Notes**                                                                                                                                             |
| ---------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------: | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 5V (CAM board 5V pin)                                      | 5V power supply (2A recommended) | **Do NOT** power CAM from 3.3V. USB power bank / 5V regulator is fine.                                                                                |
| GND                                                        |                              GND | Common ground — mandatory.                                                                                                                            |
| U0TXD (GPIO1) on CAM                                       |              RX2 (GPIO16) on DEV | CAM → DEV (camera JPEG stream)                                                                                                                        |
| U0RXD (GPIO3) on CAM                                       |              TX2 (GPIO17) on DEV | DEV → CAM (commands: PAUSE/SAVE/RESUME)                                                                                                               |
| (If using external flash LED) FLASH_PIN on CAM (eg. GPIO4) |                                — | Set in CAM code (default FLASH_PIN = 4). If using onboard LED on DEV, set FLASH_PIN in DEV code.                                                      |
| TFT SPI pins (SCK / MOSI / MISO / CS / DC / RST)           |               ESP32-DEV SPI pins | TFT wiring depends on TFT_eSPI User_Setup; common pins: SCK=18, MOSI=23, MISO=19, CS=5, DC=16 (but check your config). **Do not** connect TFT to CAM. |
| BOOT button (esp32-dev)                                    |        BOOT (GPIO0) on DEV board | Use the existing DEV board boot button (internal) to trigger save.                                                                                    |
